&lt;p&gt;Are you dynamic, self motivated, enthusiastic, and looking for the opportunity to develop your nursing career in the community setting?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a high achieving, hard working and innovative nurse to join our Long Term Conditions community nursing service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be an excellent communicator, have the ability to work autonomously whilst also being part of a team working with an integrated approach to care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will provide high quality clinical care, support and case management for patients in the primary care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be a level one registered nurse with:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Experience in community nursing&lt;br /&gt;• Evidence of continuing professional development&lt;br /&gt;• Demonstrable nursing experience.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be able to travel throughout the working day across the borough&lt;/p&gt;
